The files: 

mom_ed#.raw and se_ed#.raw

contain the data moments, by quintile, and standard errors, for each
education group ed#, (1-4)

The 5 colums refer to the five quintiles of the type distribution
(estimated by max observed wage)

The 15 rows refer to the following moments:

1  E2U - Employed to Unemployed transition rate (weekly)
2  U2E - Unemployed to Employed transition rate (weekly)
3  J2J - Job to Job transition rate (weekly)
4  DwEUE - Mean wage change via unemployment
5  DwEE  - Mean annual wage growth at same job
6  DwJ2J - Mean Wage change at job change
7  variance of DwEUE
8  variance of DwEE
9  variance of DwJ2J
10 mean log wage (average annual wage)
11 var log wage
12 mean change in log wage (year over year)
13 variance of change in log wage
14 covariance of change in log wage and lagged change in log wage
15 covariance of change in log wage and second lagged change in log
   wage



 
